# SaaS Business Model

Financial model for a B2B SaaS product with a
team of {{headcount}} people.

An agent researched current exchange rates and inserted them
into the frontmatter above for accurate currency conversion.

## Revenue

monthly_users = 2500 customers
price = $49
monthly_revenue = price * monthly_users
annual_revenue = monthly_revenue * 12

Enterprise tier adds 20% on top:

enterprise_uplift = annual_revenue + 20%

## Revenue Growth

Project revenue 3 years out at {{growth_rate}} annual growth,
compounded monthly for accuracy:

year_1 = compound annual_revenue by @globals.growth_rate monthly over 1 year
year_2 = compound annual_revenue by @globals.growth_rate monthly over 2 years
year_3 = compound annual_revenue by @globals.growth_rate monthly over 3 years

## Team Costs

avg_salary = $135000
fully_loaded = avg_salary + 25%
team_cost = fully_loaded * @globals.headcount
monthly_team_cost = team_cost / 12

## Infrastructure

hosting = $8500
hosting_annual = hosting * 12

Infrastructure cost grows ~8% per year with usage:

hosting_year_3 = compound hosting_annual by 8% over 3 years

## Equipment Depreciation

Laptops and office equipment lose value on a declining balance:

equipment = $48000
depreciate equipment by 25% over 3 years

## European Sales Office

The EU sales office invoices in euros -- exchange rates in frontmatter
were researched by the agent at current market rates:

eu_monthly = €4500
eu_monthly_usd = eu_monthly in USD
eu_annual = eu_monthly_usd * 12

UK partner agreement is invoiced in pounds:

uk_monthly = £2200
uk_monthly_usd = uk_monthly in USD
uk_annual = uk_monthly_usd * 12

## Unit Economics

cac = $850
ltv_months = 24
ltv = price * ltv_months
ltv_cac = number(ltv) / number(cac) as napkin

monthly_churn = monthly_users * 4%

## Gross Margin

total_costs = team_cost + hosting_annual + eu_annual + uk_annual
gross_profit = annual_revenue - total_costs

## Runway

current_cash = $2.4M
monthly_burn = monthly_team_cost + hosting + eu_monthly_usd + uk_monthly_usd
runway = number(current_cash) / number(monthly_burn) as napkin

## Executive Summary

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Annual Revenue | {{annual_revenue}} |
| Year 3 Projection | {{year_3}} |
| Team Cost | {{team_cost}} |
| Gross Profit | {{gross_profit}} |
| LTV:CAC | {{ltv_cac}}x |
| Monthly Burn | {{monthly_burn}} |
| Runway | {{runway}} months |

With {{monthly_users}} paying {{price}}/month, the business
generates {{annual_revenue}} annually. Compounded monthly at
{{growth_rate}}, year 3 revenue reaches {{year_3}}.
At {{monthly_burn}}/month burn with {{current_cash}} cash,
the runway is {{runway}} months.
